'''Hendrik Daniel Petrus Dames''' (born 7 February 1986 in [[Koës]])<ref name="Danie Dames on World Cup and beer with Bakkies">{{cite web | url=http://www.nwu.ac.za/content/051e-potchefstroomcampus-news-danie-dames-world-cup-and-beer-bakkies | title=Danie Dames on World Cup and beer with Bakkies | work=NWU Pukke | accessdate=1 May 2014}}</ref> is a [[Namibia]]n international [[rugby union]] player, who most recently played with {{Rut Griquas}}.<ref name="SARU Player Profile Danie Dames">{{SA Rugby Player Profile | id=35793 | name=Danie Dames | date=30 May 2016}}</ref> He can play as a winger or a full-back.

==Career==

===Youth===

Dames represented the {{Rut Griquas}} side at the 2004 [[Craven Week]] tournament in [[Nelspruit]]. The following year, Dames was a member of the [[Namibia national under-19 rugby union team|Namibia Under-19]] squad that participated in the [[2005 Under 19 Rugby World Championship]] in [[Durban]].<ref name="No opponents for under 19 rugby World Cup side">{{cite web | url=http://www.namibian.com.na/indexx.php?archive_id=13199&page_type=archive_story_detail&page=5918 | title=No opponents for under 19 rugby World Cup side | work=The Namibian | date=14 January 2005 | accessdate=1 May 2014}}</ref>

He then moved to [[Potchefstroom]], where he played for the {{Rut Leopards U19}} side in 2005 and for the {{Rut Leopards U21}} side in 2006, before joining [[Durban]]-based side the {{Rut Sharks (Currie Cup)}}, where he played for the {{Rut Sharks U21}} side in 2007.

===Sharks===

He made his senior bow in 2008, playing for the Sharks' [[Vodacom Cup]] side, the {{Rut Natal Wildebeest}} in the [[2008 Vodacom Cup]] competition, his debut coming in their match against the {{Rut Pumas}} in [[Durban]].<ref name="Wildebeest 10-30 Pumas">{{SA Rugby Match Centre | id=15182 | homeid=6606 | awayid=6597 | leagueid=618 | hometeam=Wildebeest | homescore=10 | awayscore=30 | awayteam=Pumas | matchdate=23 February 2008 | date=4 July 2016}}</ref> He made eight appearances in the competition, one in a [[Currie Cup]] pre-season compulsory friendly match against the {{Rut Griffons}}<ref name="Griffons 15-44 The Sharks">{{SA Rugby Match Centre | id=15700 | homeid=6870 | awayid=6871 | leagueid=632 | hometeam=Griffons | homescore=15 | awayscore=44 | awayteam=The Sharks | matchdate=13 June 2008 | date=4 July 2016}}</ref> and a further four for the {{Rut Sharks XV}} in the [[2009 Vodacom Cup]], but failed to establish himself in the [[Currie Cup]] side.

===Leopards===

He returned to the {{Rut Leopards}} for the [[2009 Currie Cup Premier Division]]. He remained in Potchefstroom for 5 years, scoring 27 tries in 65 appearances for the Leopards in the [[Currie Cup]] and [[Vodacom Cup]] competitions.

===Griquas===

At the end of 2013, Dames joined [[Kimberley, Northern Cape|Kimberley]]-based side {{Rut Griquas}}.<ref name="Stut-skok vir GW, Cheetahs">{{cite web | url=http://www.beeld.com/sport/2013-08-15-stut-skok-vir-gw-cheetahs | title=Stut-skok vir GW, Cheetahs | publisher=Beeld | work=Media24 | date=15 August 2013 | accessdate=16 August 2013 | language=Afrikaans}}</ref>

===International===

Dames was also a member of the {{nrut|Namibia}} squad for the [[2011 Rugby World Cup]] in [[New Zealand]], where he started 4 matches.<ref name="ESPN Scrum Player Profile: Danie Dames">{{cite web | url=http://www.espn.co.uk/scrum/rugby/player/120085.html | title=ESPN Scrum Player Profile: Danie Dames | work=ESPN Scrum | accessdate=1 May 2014}}</ref>

